01:08:26,429 --> 01:08:27,931
You are!

745
01:08:28,098 --> 01:08:32,519
Are you retarded, or just brain-dead
from whiffing fumes out in the swamp?

746
01:08:32,686 --> 01:08:37,399
That's what I am to you, isn't it?
Swamp trash, just like my mom.

747
01:08:38,650 --> 01:08:39,860
Don't!

748
01:08:43,697 --> 01:08:46,074
You stupid cunt!

749
01:09:18,273 --> 01:09:20,650
You are scared, aren't you?

750
01:10:45,360 --> 01:10:48,864
Ray! Jesus Christ!

751
01:10:49,239 --> 01:10:51,241
- Are you crazy?
- Hear her say "Sam"?

752
01:10:51,533 --> 01:10:54,619
That was Lombardo on the phone.
And you saw the two girls.

753
01:10:54,828 --> 01:10:57,122
The conversation on the tape
is unintelligible.

754
01:10:57,330 --> 01:10:59,916
What we have here is you
on the Van Ryan property...

755
01:11:00,083 --> 01:11:02,919
...shooting a porn flick!
- I can't believe this.

756
01:11:03,086 --> 01:11:06,006
A month ago, they threw things
at each other in court.

757
01:11:06,173 --> 01:11:08,800
They were acting!
They were all acting!

758
01:11:09,009 --> 01:11:10,802
We bought it, hook, line and sinker.

759
01:11:11,011 --> 01:11:13,930
They're getting away with $8 million
from Sandra Van Ryan.

760
01:11:14,097 --> 01:11:16,808
She might have saved it
if she didn't try to ruin him.

761
01:11:16,975 --> 01:11:20,187
You wouldn't go after a guy
you thought raped your daughter?

762
01:11:20,353 --> 01:11:22,689
She bought the same
goddamn story we did!

763
01:11:22,856 --> 01:11:26,735
Both of you, you're not on a case,
because there is no fucking case!

764
01:11:27,194 --> 01:11:30,405
I've had it with Sandra Van Ryan,
and you keep mucking around...

765
01:11:30,572 --> 01:11:33,074
...and she's gonna sue us
for invasion of privacy.

766
01:11:33,241 --> 01:11:35,827
So get out of these people's lives!
Hey! Ray!

767
01:11:36,703 --> 01:11:40,540
- Hey! Am I getting through?
- You think this is just about money?

768
01:11:40,707 --> 01:11:42,834
About us looking stupid?
Question him.

769
01:11:43,960 --> 01:11:48,173
You'll find a manipulative psychopath,
and those girls will wind up dead.

770
01:11:48,340 --> 01:11:49,716
Give him something to do.

771
01:11:49,883 --> 01:11:52,552
- Look into the Kennedy assassination.
- I understand.

772
01:11:52,719 --> 01:11:55,263
Next time this fucking piece of shit...

773
01:11:55,430 --> 01:11:57,474
...drags me down here,
I'm gonna sue you.

774
01:11:57,641 --> 01:11:59,976
You're goddamn lucky
I didn't sue last time.

775
01:12:00,185 --> 01:12:02,229
- I agree.
- Am I free to go?

776
01:12:02,395 --> 01:12:04,606
- Yes.
- Thank you.

777
01:12:06,900 --> 01:12:09,736
- Cocksucker.
- Yeah, what was that?

778
01:12:09,903 --> 01:12:13,573
- You heard me, motherfucker.
- Yeah, you wanna say that to my face?

779
01:12:17,244 --> 01:12:18,954
What are you looking at?

780
01:13:02,998 --> 01:13:06,376
- I guess I kind of lost it out there.
- You could say that.

781
01:13:10,797 --> 01:13:13,884
Were you ever in a situation
where you saw something coming...

782
01:13:14,050 --> 01:13:16,386
...and you didn't do
what you could to stop it?

783
01:13:16,970 --> 01:13:18,346
We all have.

784
01:13:18,513 --> 01:13:22,392
I mean something bad that you
saw coming, and then it happened...

785
01:13:22,976 --> 01:13:26,188
...and you...
You didn't do anything, and...

786
01:13:30,317 --> 01:13:32,110
I did that once.

787
01:13:34,154 --> 01:13:36,281
I don't wanna do it again.

788
01:13:55,091 --> 01:13:57,385
I thought we were going to a movie.

789
01:13:59,763 --> 01:14:02,682
I think we just need to get wasted.

790
01:14:03,350 --> 01:14:04,976
Yeah.

791
01:14:22,828 --> 01:14:24,371
Come on.

792
01:14:31,211 --> 01:14:33,839
I wanna live at the beach someday.

793
01:14:34,214 --> 01:14:35,882
Oh, shit.

794
01:14:36,049 --> 01:14:38,760
I left the keys.

795
01:14:38,927 --> 01:14:40,512
I'll get them.

796
01:15:00,282 --> 01:15:01,658
Kelly?

797
01:15:01,825 --> 01:15:03,452
Suzie.

798
01:15:05,954 --> 01:15:07,706
It's me.

799
01:15:12,544 --> 01:15:15,505
I was worried about you,
and I decided...

800
01:15:15,672 --> 01:15:19,926
...the three of us should get together
one last time before we split up.

801
01:15:20,552 --> 01:15:23,472
- Are you mad at me?
- No, no.

802
01:15:23,638 --> 01:15:26,099
I probably should've told you
a bit more about...

803
01:15:26,266 --> 01:15:28,560
...the part I intended to play.

804
01:15:28,727 --> 01:15:30,645
But we'll go through it again tonight.

805
01:15:34,941 --> 01:15:38,862
This is a celebration, Suzie,
not a suicide pact.

806
01:15:39,112 --> 01:15:42,991
We're gonna chill out
and just relax...

807
01:15:43,158 --> 01:15:45,702
...have a little champagne...

808
01:15:45,869 --> 01:15:47,662
...watch the stars...

809
01:15:48,789 --> 01:15:50,081
Kelly?

810
01:15:50,290 --> 01:15:52,918
You got a blanket in the back
of your mom's Rover?

811
01:15:54,044 --> 01:15:57,047
Why don't you be an angel
and run over and get it for us?

812
01:15:59,633 --> 01:16:01,301
Good girl.

813
01:16:02,969 --> 01:16:05,472
Let me tell you about the boat
I picked out for us.

814
01:17:08,827 --> 01:17:10,495
You okay?

815
01:17:12,038 --> 01:17:15,333
My mom would kill me
if she knew I took the Rover.

816
01:18:15,852 --> 01:18:17,062
Been four-wheeling?

817
01:18:18,772 --> 01:18:21,274
- Get off my property!
- I'm not on your property.

818
01:18:21,441 --> 01:18:24,611
- Lf you don't get out of here...
- You'll call a cop? I am a cop!

819
01:18:25,237 --> 01:18:26,446
Goddamn it!

820
01:18:48,426 --> 01:18:50,595
So you say she didn't
come home last night.

821
01:18:50,762 --> 01:18:55,058
She's been talking about going to L.A.,
but her clothes are all still here.

822
01:18:55,225 --> 01:18:58,270
Walter! You get sick,
it'll serve you right.

823
01:19:01,064 --> 01:19:04,192
Found some teeth in an old trailer
down the road.

824
01:19:04,359 --> 01:19:06,444
He says they'll fit.

825
01:19:06,903 --> 01:19:10,574
Suzie hasn't been back to school
since the trial.

826
01:19:10,740 --> 01:19:14,453
Oh, and now they're saying
that she can't graduate.

827
01:19:14,619 --> 01:19:18,665
It is that Kelly Van Ryan that got her
into this whole mess, and you know it.

828
01:19:18,832 --> 01:19:21,042
Well, we'll look into it for you, Ruby.

829
01:19:21,209 --> 01:19:24,212
We find something,
you'll be the first to know.

830
01:19:25,672 --> 01:19:27,090
Come on.

831
01:19:45,525 --> 01:19:47,944
It's starting, Gloria.
This is how it begins.

832
01:19:48,111 --> 01:19:51,239
Ray, we don't know anything yet.
She could be anywhere.

833
01:19:51,406 --> 01:19:53,909
I'll drop you off.
Put a call out on Suzie's car.

834
01:19:54,075 --> 01:19:55,702
You got someplace you wanna be?

835
01:19:56,536 --> 01:19:59,790
- You got a date?
- Just check the car out for me.

836
01:20:09,549 --> 01:20:11,843
It's over here, by that old boat.

837
01:20:12,969 --> 01:20:15,639
So you and Suzie used to
come out here together?

838
01:20:15,806 --> 01:20:17,724
Yeah, sometimes.

839
01:20:17,891 --> 01:20:20,310
A lot of the kids hang out here.

840
01:20:21,895 --> 01:20:24,648
You really think something bad
happened to Suzie?

841
01:20:25,190 --> 01:20:27,359
Lombardo ever come out here?

842
01:20:29,653 --> 01:20:31,363
I say something funny?

843
01:20:31,571 --> 01:20:35,742
No, but I mean, just the idea
that Mr. Lombardo would...

844
01:20:35,909 --> 01:20:39,496
Well, the way I heard it,
he was pretty tight with the kids.

845
01:20:39,663 --> 01:20:41,206
You and him were pals, right?

846
01:20:41,373 --> 01:20:44,626
Yeah, but he got me
onto the sailing team.

847
01:20:44,793 --> 01:20:47,754
Told me I could work my way
through college, like he did.

848
01:20:47,921 --> 01:20:51,842
Sam Lombardo went to the University
of Miami on an athletic scholarship.

849
01:20:52,008 --> 01:20:55,971
Boats didn't have a damn thing
to do with it.

850
01:21:46,521 --> 01:21:48,523
Listen, I'm gonna be here a while, kid.

851
01:21:48,690 --> 01:21:51,526
Why don't you go up to the highway
and catch the bus?

852
01:21:57,365 --> 01:21:58,992
Hey, Jimmy.

853
01:22:01,203 --> 01:22:05,665
People aren't always what they
appear to be. Don't forget that.

854
01:22:23,099 --> 01:22:25,393
- This is where they did it.
- Where's the body?

855
01:22:25,560 --> 01:22:27,646
The swamp, most likely.
Guy's a swamp rat.

856
01:22:27,854 --> 01:22:30,315
He knows it won't be found,
but he made a mistake.

857
01:22:30,524 --> 01:22:34,319
She'd been threatening to run away
and I found the car at the bus terminal.

858
01:22:34,486 --> 01:22:36,154
You don't think Sam put it there?

859
01:22:36,363 --> 01:22:39,574
Hold on a second.
Gloria, have the car dusted for prints.

860
01:22:39,741 --> 01:22:43,161
And if Suzie even was murdered,
it was that damn Van Ryan kid.

861
01:22:43,328 --> 01:22:45,497
Little sociopath's the one
who started this.

862
01:22:45,705 --> 01:22:48,750
- How long till we get something?
- We can get blood type now.

863
01:22:48,917 --> 01:22:52,420
Dental records will take longer.
DNA could take weeks.

864
01:22:54,047 --> 01:22:56,007
Poor, dumb Suzie.
Kid never had a chance.

865
01:22:56,216 --> 01:22:58,844
- We don't know that.
- I'm telling you, Kelly's next.

866
01:22:59,052 --> 01:23:02,848
I'm telling you, you get
off this right now.

867
01:23:03,098 --> 01:23:07,269
Don't even fucking let me hear
about you bothering Lombardo.

868
01:23:10,730 --> 01:23:12,232
David!

869
01:23:12,399 --> 01:23:14,776
You get an ID, you call me!

870
01:23:17,154 --> 01:23:18,363
Will you do me a favor?

871
01:23:19,573 --> 01:23:21,199
Ray, you heard him.

872
01:23:21,366 --> 01:23:24,327
He told me to stay away.
He didn't say anything about you.

873
01:23:24,494 --> 01:23:26,997
What if I'm right and Hunter's wrong?

874
01:23:27,164 --> 01:23:29,624
Please, you gotta help me out
on this, partner.

875
01:23:30,041 --> 01:23:33,336
And if the teeth aren't Suzie's,
you'll give this up?

876
01:23:34,588 --> 01:23:38,508
If I'm wrong about those teeth,
you got my word.

877
01:24:21,968 --> 01:24:24,679
- Hello?
- I've been calling you.

878
01:24:24,846 --> 01:24:26,640
- I wanna see you.
- Where are you?

879
01:24:26,807 --> 01:24:29,476
- The stupid guest house.
- Good. Stay there.

880
01:24:29,643 --> 01:24:31,436
Sam, I'm really nervous.

881
01:24:31,978 --> 01:24:34,231
Kelly, relax.

882
01:24:34,523 --> 01:24:36,983
Take one of your mom's
Valiums or something.

883
01:24:37,150 --> 01:24:40,862
In a week, you get on the plane,
this is over. We're rich.

884
01:24:41,029 --> 01:24:43,156
But what if they find out?

885
01:24:43,490 --> 01:24:46,201
My God, they'd put you
in the electric chair.

886
01:24:46,368 --> 01:24:47,828
Look, Kelly...

887
01:24:47,994 --> 01:24:50,872
...stay in the guest house,
skip the graduation parties.

888
01:24:51,331 --> 01:24:53,583
I love you so much.

889
01:24:53,750 --> 01:24:55,710
And I love you too, Kelly.

890
01:24:55,877 --> 01:24:57,838
Be a good girl
and stay where you are.

891
01:25:21,027 --> 01:25:23,488
Peeping in people's windows?

892
01:25:24,197 --> 01:25:25,615
Isn't that against the law?

893
01:25:27,492 --> 01:25:29,244
Suzie Toller's missing.

894
01:25:30,328 --> 01:25:32,956
- Since when?
- She didn't come home last night.

895
01:25:33,290 --> 01:25:36,084
We found her car
at the bus terminal.

896
01:25:36,376 --> 01:25:38,044
Ray thinks she was murdered.

897
01:25:38,795 --> 01:25:40,922
Well, I don't know what to tell you.

898
01:25:42,674 --> 01:25:45,510
You could tell me
where you were last night.

899
01:25:46,052 --> 01:25:49,306
I suppose I could,
but I don't really have to, now, do I?

900
01:25:52,392 --> 01:25:53,643
Come here.

901
01:25:54,978 --> 01:25:57,105
I wanna show you something.

902
01:26:08,366 --> 01:26:10,410
Looks like goodbye.

903
01:26:11,077 --> 01:26:12,871
Kelly's file.

904
01:26:13,079 --> 01:26:16,875
Read it. You're gonna find an angry,
sexually confused girl...

905
01:26:17,042 --> 01:26:19,544
...who threatened the lives
of at least two people.

906
01:26:19,753 --> 01:26:21,171
What two people?

907
01:26:21,338 --> 01:26:23,548
One of them was her mother.

908
01:26:23,757 --> 01:26:25,759
The other one was...

909
01:26:27,135 --> 01:26:28,678
...a female classmate...

910
01:26:30,263 --> 01:26:32,933
...she may have been
sexually involved with.

911
01:26:34,059 --> 01:26:35,560
Suzie?

912
01:26:37,270 --> 01:26:39,231
Now you got the file.

913
01:26:39,731 --> 01:26:41,149
Read it.

914
01:26:41,983 --> 01:26:45,153
I think it'll give you a new
perspective on things.

915
01:26:46,279 --> 01:26:49,658
Why didn't you tell us about this
before the trial?

916
01:26:51,701 --> 01:26:54,496
Because then I had principles.

917
01:26:54,663 --> 01:26:56,498
That meant a lot to me.

918
01:26:58,542 --> 01:26:59,960
Now...

919
01:27:01,461 --> 01:27:03,380
...I don't care.

920
01:27:17,477 --> 01:27:19,729
I should probably go now.

921
01:27:22,357 --> 01:27:25,318
Unless you're planning
on holding me for something.

922
01:27:52,804 --> 01:27:55,765
- Duquette. What's happening?
- I'm tired. I'm going home.

923
01:27:55,974 --> 01:27:57,434
- Where's Lombardo?
- He's gone.

924
01:27:57,642 --> 01:28:00,812
Goddamn it, Gloria, the blood type
on the rocks matches Suzie's.

925
01:28:01,021 --> 01:28:03,064
Let me tell you something, Ray:

926
01:28:03,231 --> 01:28:05,275
There's more to this story
than you know.

927
01:28:05,442 --> 01:28:06,985
If Suzie is dead...

928
01:28:07,194 --> 01:28:09,613
...Hunter may be on
the right track about Kelly.

929
01:28:11,823 --> 01:28:13,325
Ray?

930
01:28:14,534 --> 01:28:16,953
Shit, Ray.

931
01:28:26,254 --> 01:28:29,382
- Who is it?
- It's Detective Duquette.

932
01:28:29,549 --> 01:28:31,426
Open the gate, now.

933
01:29:02,791 --> 01:29:04,960
- Hello, Kelly.
- What are you doing here?

934
01:29:23,270 --> 01:29:26,690
Where's...? Kelly! Kelly!

935
01:29:34,281 --> 01:29:38,034
I just looked away for a second,
just a split second.

936
01:29:38,326 --> 01:29:41,121
And just like that, bingo...

937
01:29:41,455 --> 01:29:43,665
...she put a knee in my groin.

938
01:29:43,832 --> 01:29:46,626
I didn't go down,
but it slowed me down...

939
01:29:47,127 --> 01:29:48,879
...just enough.

940
01:29:49,463 --> 01:29:51,465
I couldn't get to her.

941
01:29:52,299 --> 01:29:54,342
She turned on me with the gun.

942
01:29:56,470 --> 01:29:58,638
Fired one shot.

943
01:29:59,639 --> 01:30:01,266
I took the hit in the shoulder.

944
01:30:04,644 --> 01:30:06,605
I had no choice.

945
01:30:10,484 --> 01:30:11,776
I had to return fire.

946
01:30:13,528 --> 01:30:17,115
Two rounds, I think,
in the chest.

947
01:30:20,869 --> 01:30:23,121
I went there to protect her.

948
01:30:25,999 --> 01:30:28,543
I went... I went there to protect her.

949
01:30:28,710 --> 01:30:30,462
Detective Duquette.

950
01:30:30,629 --> 01:30:34,132
I spent time in military intelligence,
and we had a saying there:

951
01:30:34,341 --> 01:30:37,594
"Once is happenstance.
Twice is coincidence.

952
01:30:37,761 --> 01:30:39,846
Three times is enemy action."

953
01:30:40,013 --> 01:30:42,057
This is twice for you, Duquette...

954
01:30:42,224 --> 01:30:45,519
...and I intend to see to it
that there is no third time.

955
01:30:46,019 --> 01:30:49,856
Our investigation finds that this was
a good shooting, but that's irrelevant.

956
01:30:50,023 --> 01:30:52,776
You ignored the advice
of your superiors.

957
01:30:52,943 --> 01:30:55,821
Consequently,
two young women are dead.

958
01:30:56,404 --> 01:31:00,492
You are, as of now, terminated,
with forfeiture of pension and benefits.

959
01:31:00,659 --> 01:31:02,327
Chief Goodsall...

960
01:31:02,494 --> 01:31:06,706
...Detective Duquette found
Susan Marie Toller's teeth and blood...

961
01:31:06,873 --> 01:31:09,376
...near the area known as
Stoner Beach.

962
01:31:09,543 --> 01:31:12,754
Miss Toller's blood was also found
in the Van Ryan Range Rover.

963
01:31:12,921 --> 01:31:15,924
This has led this office to conclude...

964
01:31:16,258 --> 01:31:19,719
...that Susan Marie Toller was
murdered by Kelly Lanier Van Ryan.

965
01:31:20,887 --> 01:31:23,223
She...
She didn't.

966
01:31:25,684 --> 01:31:27,352
Mr. Duquette.

967
01:31:27,853 --> 01:31:29,521
Mr. Duquette.

968
01:31:29,938 --> 01:31:33,567
This investigation is concluded.
You're dismissed.

969
01:31:59,926 --> 01:32:01,678
Thank you, Paul.

970
01:32:56,441 --> 01:32:57,651
Howdy, partner.

971
01:32:59,569 --> 01:33:03,448
Jesus, man. I wasn't expecting you
until tomorrow.

972
01:33:07,160 --> 01:33:09,079
Hey, nice girlfriend you got there.

973
01:33:09,246 --> 01:33:11,748
Kelly was only supposed to be framed.

974
01:33:11,915 --> 01:33:13,792
The bitch shot me.

975
01:33:14,000 --> 01:33:17,462
Shit, you're a cop.
Don't they teach you to disarm people?

976
01:33:17,671 --> 01:33:20,132
You know, shoot them
in the leg or something?

977
01:33:20,340 --> 01:33:23,635
Did you become squeamish
about this stuff before or after...

978
01:33:23,844 --> 01:33:27,055
...you bludgeoned little Suzie
to death with a wine bottle?

979
01:33:27,222 --> 01:33:30,684
Kelly wasn't supposed to die, Ray.
It wasn't part of the plan.

980
01:33:30,851 --> 01:33:35,355
It couldn't have worked out better.
They're convinced Kelly killed Suzie.

981
01:33:35,522 --> 01:33:37,357
I couldn't talk them out of it.

982
01:33:37,524 --> 01:33:39,526
I'm telling you,
I don't like surprises.

983
01:33:39,734 --> 01:33:43,697
Look at it this way:
Every cloud has a silver lining.

984
01:33:43,864 --> 01:33:45,782
Now there's no loose ends.

985
01:33:45,949 --> 01:33:49,453
Come tomorrow,
you'll never see me again.

986
01:33:49,619 --> 01:33:53,123
Oh, listen, about tomorrow...

987
01:33:53,540 --> 01:33:57,252
...I spoke to the bank and they said
it's gonna take two working days...

988
01:33:58,462 --> 01:34:00,255
...to make the transfer, so...

989
01:34:00,422 --> 01:34:01,965
- Bullshit.
- Oh, yeah.

990
01:34:02,132 --> 01:34:03,842
Call them yourself.

991
01:34:04,217 --> 01:34:08,346
Anyway, what's your hurry?
Kick back for a day or two.

992
01:34:08,513 --> 01:34:12,517
We'll take out the boat.
I just had it outfitted.

993
01:34:13,101 --> 01:34:14,978
I could use a deck hand.

994
01:34:20,400 --> 01:34:22,903
Here's to large bank accounts.

995
01:34:25,280 --> 01:34:28,784
You gotta lighten up, partner.
You're a rich man.

996
01:34:32,078 --> 01:34:35,248
To large accounts
and no loose ends.

997
01:34:36,166 --> 01:34:38,043
And no loose ends.

998
01:34:56,436 --> 01:34:59,314
Hey, Ray, you see that winch?

999
01:35:00,816 --> 01:35:03,068
Take a couple turns on it.
She's luffing.

1000
01:35:07,823 --> 01:35:09,491
- You mean that thing?
- Yeah, Ray.

1001
01:35:09,658 --> 01:35:13,787
We call it a winch.
It's what we use to tighten the sails.

1002
01:35:13,954 --> 01:35:18,083
- So why don't you start cranking?
- This is supposed to be a vacation.

1003
01:35:18,291 --> 01:35:20,252
Why don't you get a nice powerboat?

1004
01:35:20,961 --> 01:35:23,588
Come on, Ray.
I'll make a sailor out of you yet.

1005
01:35:24,548 --> 01:35:26,383
Or get me drowned.

1006
01:35:40,480 --> 01:35:41,731
It's stuck.

1007
01:35:41,898 --> 01:35:45,110
What do you mean, it's stuck?
Put a little elbow grease in it.

1008
01:35:49,406 --> 01:35:50,991
It's stuck, I'm telling you.

1009
01:35:52,868 --> 01:35:55,120
The jenny sheet must be
caught on something.

1010
01:35:55,328 --> 01:35:58,582
Why don't you go starboard
and see if you can unhook it?

1011
01:35:58,748 --> 01:36:02,252
- I don't understand a word you said.
- Okay, Ray.

1012
01:36:02,419 --> 01:36:05,380
You see this line right here?
Follow it down...

1013
01:36:05,547 --> 01:36:08,175
...and see if you can see
what it's snagged on.

1014
01:36:09,968 --> 01:36:11,511
You're killing me.

1015
01:36:20,270 --> 01:36:24,232
- You mean this thing?
- That's it. That one right there.

1016
01:36:24,649 --> 01:36:26,610
You see anything?

1017
01:36:29,571 --> 01:36:31,448
Look a little lower.

1018
01:36:31,698 --> 01:36:32,949
That's it.

1019
01:36:42,042 --> 01:36:44,544
Guess I forgot to tell you, Ray:

1020
01:36:46,254 --> 01:36:48,757
One hand for the boat,
the other one for yourself.

1021
01:36:49,174 --> 01:36:51,301
First rule of sailing.

1022
01:37:16,576 --> 01:37:17,869
Ray!

1023
01:37:18,036 --> 01:37:20,664
- What happened?
- Nice try, motherfucker!

1024
01:37:29,798 --> 01:37:31,424
You!

1025
01:37:32,092 --> 01:37:34,052
You're dead!

1026
01:37:34,261 --> 01:37:35,762
No, I'm not.

1027
01:37:38,431 --> 01:37:39,850
Sam.

1028
01:37:40,016 --> 01:37:43,520
- Sam, for chrissake!
- Sorry, partner.

1029
01:37:43,687 --> 01:37:46,231
You really shouldn't have killed Kelly.

1030
01:37:46,439 --> 01:37:49,776
You shouldn't have killed that kid
out in the glades either.

1031
01:37:49,943 --> 01:37:52,779
- What was his name?
- Davy.

1032
01:38:05,959 --> 01:38:07,586
That's my son, Walter.

1033
01:38:07,752 --> 01:38:12,841
He's been doing this a long time,
so don't be afraid. Please, come on in.

1034
01:38:13,008 --> 01:38:16,428
Thank you so much
for coming down to the glades.

1035
01:38:29,399 --> 01:38:34,279
Did you come here to watch Walter,
or is this an official visit?

1036
01:38:34,571 --> 01:38:36,740
No. Actually, it's my day off.

1037
01:38:38,575 --> 01:38:40,285
I thought you looked different.

1038
01:38:40,494 --> 01:38:43,038
I came because I was hoping
you would talk to me.

1039
01:38:44,581 --> 01:38:45,874
About Suzie?

1040
01:38:46,041 --> 01:38:49,795
Actually, I was wondering if you would
talk to me about Ray Duquette.

1041
01:38:55,258 --> 01:38:57,761
He used to come around here.

1042
01:38:58,637 --> 01:39:01,973
He had a thing going
with one of the girls...

1043
01:39:02,182 --> 01:39:05,727
Girls. Over at the glades.

1044
01:39:06,561 --> 01:39:10,148
Got sort of hung up on her,
from what I hear.

1045
01:39:10,899 --> 01:39:14,653
- She still work there?
- Not after that night.

1046
01:39:15,195 --> 01:39:17,364
All I know is, the next morning...

1047
01:39:17,531 --> 01:39:21,493
...she was gone and a boy was dead.

1048
01:39:21,660 --> 01:39:27,082
Seminole kid named Davy.
He had a crush on Ray's whore.

1049
01:39:30,460 --> 01:39:34,714
Caught Ray slapping her around,
and he tried to stop it.

1050
01:39:35,715 --> 01:39:38,593
So Ray killed him.

1051
01:39:39,386 --> 01:39:41,596
Suzie saw it.

1052
01:39:41,930 --> 01:39:45,809
So he busted her and sent her up.

1053
01:39:45,976 --> 01:39:50,647
You know, just to prove that he could.

1054
01:39:51,398 --> 01:39:54,442
That's all there is to say
about Ray Duquette.

1055
01:40:05,579 --> 01:40:07,581
To Ray.

1056
01:40:07,914 --> 01:40:11,543
We won. Sam, it's over.

1057
01:40:19,050 --> 01:40:23,388
Wow. Talk about paranoid.
Take a look around us, Sam.

1058
01:40:23,555 --> 01:40:27,726
You're gonna have to teach me how to
drive this before I can get rid of you.

1059
01:40:39,404 --> 01:40:40,780
Okay, Toller.

1060
01:40:40,947 --> 01:40:43,700
I wanna trim the sail.
Grab a hold of that winch.

1061
01:40:44,618 --> 01:40:48,455
- Fuck the winch. I wanna drive.
- It doesn't work that way.

1062
01:40:48,622 --> 01:40:50,749
You don't drive it, you sail it.

1063
01:40:51,792 --> 01:40:53,960
Now, get on that winch.

1064
01:40:55,128 --> 01:40:58,006
I just wanna cruise for a while.

1065
01:41:01,635 --> 01:41:06,223
That's funny. That's one of the first
things I noticed about you, Sam.

1066
01:41:06,389 --> 01:41:09,267
You like to cruise.

1067
01:41:10,936 --> 01:41:14,773
- Suzie.
- Take college, for instance.

1068
01:41:14,981 --> 01:41:19,945
I bet the classes you took were ones
where the finals were multiple choice.

1069
01:41:20,737 --> 01:41:24,407
And you never bought the book.
You'd find a girl to loan you hers.

1070
01:41:24,574 --> 01:41:28,286
And then, of course, you'd have
to fuck her after that, right?

1071
01:41:28,495 --> 01:41:29,955
Is that how it went?

1072
01:41:32,958 --> 01:41:34,417
Yeah.

1073
01:41:36,795 --> 01:41:39,631
Well, I've got a good pop quiz for you.

1074
01:41:39,798 --> 01:41:41,883
Multiple choice, of course.

1075
01:41:43,218 --> 01:41:44,886
Before sailing on the Helios...

1076
01:41:45,053 --> 01:41:50,642
...Medea killed King Creon
and the princess with what?

1077
01:41:51,143 --> 01:41:52,769
A rock?

1078
01:41:53,687 --> 01:41:55,397
A spear gun?

1079
01:41:57,440 --> 01:41:58,984
Or a little poison?

1080
01:41:59,860 --> 01:42:01,987
Poison!

1081
01:42:05,782 --> 01:42:07,325
Good guess.

1082
01:42:21,506 --> 01:42:23,216
Van Ryan got old.

1083
01:42:23,842 --> 01:42:26,344
He and his cronies would come here.

1084
01:42:26,553 --> 01:42:30,640
Hunt and whore.
They acted like a bunch of assholes.

1085
01:42:31,016 --> 01:42:33,602
One trip, he showed up with this girl...

1086
01:42:33,768 --> 01:42:37,022
...he'd picked up somewhere.

1087
01:42:37,230 --> 01:42:39,316
Gotten her pregnant.

1088
01:42:40,358 --> 01:42:42,694
Dumped her in the swamp.

1089
01:42:43,028 --> 01:42:44,988
Poor girl was dead in a year.

1090
01:42:48,408 --> 01:42:52,245
That came with her.

1091
01:42:52,871 --> 01:42:54,623
And the child?

1092
01:42:54,790 --> 01:42:58,418
Well, she had it.
Before she drank herself to death.

1093
01:42:59,961 --> 01:43:02,964
Wasn't exactly a love child.

1094
01:43:14,100 --> 01:43:16,645
So you're not her grandmother.

1095
01:43:17,771 --> 01:43:20,816
I raised her like I was.

1096
01:43:21,358 --> 01:43:25,570
But, no. Walt was my only child.
He was a good boy.

1097
01:43:25,779 --> 01:43:27,906
Until the Army took him.

1098
01:43:28,114 --> 01:43:31,660
So Suzie and Sandra Van Ryan
were half sisters.

1099
01:43:32,202 --> 01:43:36,581
And the other girl, Kelly?
Suzie's niece.

1100
01:43:47,300 --> 01:43:51,304
Well, it may be good news or not.
I don't know. We'll start with the letter.

1101
01:43:51,471 --> 01:43:54,975
- H.
- Yes, there are two H's.

1102
01:44:18,373 --> 01:44:20,250
Nice truck.

1103
01:44:28,216 --> 01:44:29,968
Selling your boat?

1104
01:44:35,056 --> 01:44:37,350
This was Suzie's boat.

1105
01:44:38,018 --> 01:44:40,520
Guess she won't be needing it now.

1106
01:44:42,355 --> 01:44:46,401
Funny. I wouldn't have guessed
Suzie was a sailor.

1107
01:44:48,778 --> 01:44:52,949
Old lady had her tested once.
They said her IQ was way up there.

1108
01:44:53,116 --> 01:44:56,995
Around 200 or some such shit.

1109
01:44:57,162 --> 01:45:00,624
That girl could do just about
anything she put her mind to.

1110
01:46:12,362 --> 01:46:14,072
Hi.

1111
01:46:14,781 --> 01:46:16,616
What are you doing out here?

1112
01:46:17,576 --> 01:46:19,828
I'm running away.

1113
01:46:20,620 --> 01:46:22,789
You think that's wise?

1114
01:46:25,625 --> 01:46:27,961
Guess what else?

1115
01:46:31,006 --> 01:46:32,966
I have toys.

1116
01:46:38,013 --> 01:46:40,140
I suppose one taste won't hurt.

1117
01:46:51,651 --> 01:46:53,153
You know...

1118
01:46:53,320 --> 01:46:56,823
...that weekend I got busted,
I called you about a hundred times.

1119
01:47:01,495 --> 01:47:05,457
I really believed that stuff
about you being my friend.

1120
01:47:07,793 --> 01:47:09,085
Was I naive.

1121
01:47:13,590 --> 01:47:15,634
I can't decide what came out better.

1122
01:47:15,842 --> 01:47:21,181
That little straw up Kelly's nose
or that dildo shoved up her ass.

1123
01:47:22,349 --> 01:47:24,851
What do you think, Mr. Lombardo?

1124
01:47:39,199 --> 01:47:41,618
Seems to like the same places you do.

1125
01:47:42,160 --> 01:47:46,706
- Funny you never met.
- Yeah, real funny.

1126
01:47:46,873 --> 01:47:51,336
You know, you're wrong about this,
and I could get busted on the spot.

1127
01:47:52,337 --> 01:47:57,008
Trust me. The guy's dirty. He'll love it.
Especially the part about killing me.

1128
01:47:57,175 --> 01:48:00,637
Now, get out of here.
Go make yourself a new friend.

1129
01:48:12,899 --> 01:48:15,026
What are you drinking?

1130
01:48:19,114 --> 01:48:21,867
We gotta stop. I'm gonna come.

1131
01:48:23,910 --> 01:48:27,164
That never seemed
to worry you at the glades.

1132
01:48:28,748 --> 01:48:33,879
- That's not your line...
- Say you love me.

1133
01:48:35,464 --> 01:48:39,551
I love you.
Now, give me the line.

1134
01:48:39,759 --> 01:48:43,346
No little girl can ever make me come.

1135
01:48:56,943 --> 01:49:01,031
You got the pressure too tight.
You're gonna crush the evidence.

1136
01:49:05,577 --> 01:49:08,246
Oh, for chrissake.

1137
01:49:23,303 --> 01:49:25,680
- Hello, Kelly.
- What are you doing here?

1138
01:50:12,811 --> 01:50:14,688
May I ask you a question, Ms. Toller?

1139
01:50:17,232 --> 01:50:20,402
Did you enjoy being
a guest of the state?

1140
01:50:23,113 --> 01:50:24,990
I hope I never make you mad.

1141
01:50:28,910 --> 01:50:31,580
Cash is just walking-around money.

1142
01:50:32,205 --> 01:50:34,416
The check is the balance
of the numbered account...

1143
01:50:34,583 --> 01:50:37,043
...minus the million we set aside
for Ruby and Walter...

1144
01:50:37,210 --> 01:50:38,879
...less my usual fee.

1145
01:50:40,797 --> 01:50:42,466
Case closed.

1146
01:50:54,644 --> 01:50:56,438
Suzie.

1147
01:50:59,065 --> 01:51:01,067
Be good.